'''Operation Passage to Freedom''' was the name of the sea lift of anti-communist [[Vietnam]]ese out of communist-held territory following the [[Geneva]] peace agreements in [[1954]]. The period allowed under the Geneva Accords was 300 days for free movement between the two zones. Over 300,000 lives were saved by these sealifts.<Ref>[http://www.ttup.ttu.edu/BookPages/0896726088.html Operation Passage to Freedom: The United States Navy in Vietnam, 1954-1955] - Texas Tech</ref>

